fields.name: pad_code
fields.doc: First 8 bits to transmit during dummy cycles

fields.name: addr_proto
fields.doc: Protocol for transmitting address and padding

fields.name: ack
fields.doc: When a receiver, sent ACK (0) or NACK (1)

fields.name: iack
fields.doc: Interrupt acknowledge. When set, clears a pending interrupt

fields.name: rx_ack
fields.doc:
Received acknowledge from slave.
                This flag represents acknowledge from the addressed slave.
                '1' = No acknowledge received
                '0' = Acknowledge received

fields.name: if
fields.doc:
Interrupt Flag. This bit is set when an interrupt is pending, which
                will cause a processor interrupt request if the IEN bit is set.
